Two horizontal lines are parallel and $P$ lies between them. A ray from $P$ meets the upper line at $37^{\circ}$, and another ray from $P$ meets the lower line at $48^{\circ}$, as shown. By drawing an auxiliary line through $P$ parallel to the two lines, find the angle $x$ between the rays.
